Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
Then I go to Page 03 and select 'Yes' in Contrast enhanced
And I click on 'Sequences' tab
And I select 'DWI' from the 'Weighting' dropdown
Then I go to Page 06 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' radio button
And dropdown below 'Finding' is enabled

When I select 'Ovary torsion' from the dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled

And 'Right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Left' checkbox is enabled

And 'Enlargement of the central afollicular stromas' checkbox is enabled
And 'Peripheral follicular displacement' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hematoma' checkbox is enabled
And 'Focal or parietal T1w signal increase' checkbox is enabled

And 'Decreased' radio button is enabled
And 'No' radio button is enabled

And 'Diffusion restriction' checkbox is enabled

And 'Enlarged ovary' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ovarian mass' checkbox is enabled

And 'Twisted ovarian vessel' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hematosalpinx' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ipsilateral uterine deviation' checkbox is enabled

And 'Hydrosalpinx' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ascites' checkbox is enabled

And 'Differential diagnosis' dropdown is enabled

When I select 'Enlarged ovary' checkbox
Then 'T2w signal increase' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Ovarian mass' checkbox
Then 'Expansion in mm' input field is enabled

When I select 'Hydrosalpinx' checkbox
Then 'T1w signal increase' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Ascites' checkbox
Then 'T1w signal increase' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Hemosiderin' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Focal' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Generalized' checkbox is enabled

When I select any option from 'Differential diagnosis' dropdown
Then option is accepted

